# Introducing the Interstate Points Program

Every trade you place, every referral you bring in, every quest you complete on Interstate now counts toward something real: a share of the **Moonsheet** — our airdrop pool worth up to **$50M at full valuation**.

This post breaks down exactly how the program works, how to climb the ranks, and how your activity converts into tokens when the Moonsheet lands.

---

## The Two-Tier System

Interstate rewards two different things, and we use two different currencies to track them.

**Credits** measure your engagement. You earn them by trading, completing quests, referring friends, and showing up consistently. Credits level up your bird — a persistent on-platform identity that evolves as you grind.

**Points** measure your economic contribution. They're driven by the volume you push through the terminal and the fees that volume generates. Points determine the size of your Moonsheet allocation.

Your final Moonsheet score combines both:

```
POINT = (credit_multiplier × Credits) + (Volume ÷ 10)
```

Credits get you on the board. Points get you paid.

---

## Your Bird: The Leveling System

Every Interstate account is tied to a bird. Your bird starts at Level 1 and can evolve all the way to Level 300. Levels are purely a function of Credits spent — 1 Credit = 1 XP toward the next level.

The cost to advance from Level L to Level L+1 is:

```
100 × L Credits
```

So going from Level 1 → 2 costs 100 Credits. Going from 150 → 151 costs 15,000. Going from 299 → 300 costs 29,900.

Cumulative Credits to reach any level N follows a clean closed form:

```
Total Credits = 50 × N × (N − 1)
```

